We built our new house and moved in two years ago at which time we had a 420ft well drilled (first 75ft is cased). We have run 5 sprinklers at once along with having three bathrooms. In the past we changed our filters once every 2-3 months without knowing a drop in water pressure even after that time frame. For the last 2-3 months we have religiously had to change our 20 micron filters every 3 days. When it’s changed it is completely occluded, allowing only 20% water flow thru at 75psi from the pump! I am concerned that the pipeline has pierced the aquifer feeding our well, polluting it with contaminants. We are also deeply concerned that we may be subjecting ourselves to harm by consuming our water! We desperately need help to figure out what the problem is! The Sunoco Mariner pipeline drilled thru the mountain by my house to avoid I99 that crosses above. I have kept all of my filters in ziploc bags. Filters are costing me $83 a month now! Smell was reported several months to my local DEP/ Blair County Conservation Group who said they noted it and was going to send a representative out on site, never heard anything else from them and my calls are not being returned!
